## TECH STACK — STRICT RULES

- **React 18** via CDN. No npm, no webpack, no Vite, no build tools.
- **Babel Standalone** for JSX transformation in-browser.
- **All styles are inline** via JS objects in React. No CSS-in-JS libraries.
- **Minimal global CSS** only in the style tag for: resets, scrollbar, keyframe animations.
- **No external libraries** except the 3 CDN scripts above (React, ReactDOM, Babel) and Google Fonts.
- **No Tailwind, no Framer Motion, no GSAP, no D3, no Chart.js, no animation libraries.**
- All animations are pure CSS @keyframes.
- The file must work by double-clicking it in a browser. Zero setup.

