## ANIMATION SYSTEM

**Global CSS keyframes (put in style tag):**

```css
@keyframes pulse    { 0%,100% { opacity:1 } 50% { opacity:.35 } }
@keyframes slideUp  { from { opacity:0; transform:translateY(18px) } to { opacity:1; transform:translateY(0) } }
@keyframes fadeIn   { from { opacity:0 } to { opacity:1 } }
@keyframes pop      { from { opacity:0; transform:scale(0.85) } to { opacity:1; transform:scale(1) } }
```

**Staggered entrance pattern:**

```css
.slide.on .a1 { animation: slideUp .45s .05s ease both }
.slide.on .a2 { animation: slideUp .45s .15s ease both }
.slide.on .a3 { animation: slideUp .45s .25s ease both }
.slide.on .a4 { animation: slideUp .45s .35s ease both }
.slide.on .a5 { animation: slideUp .45s .45s ease both }
```

**Rules:**

- Every card/section entrance uses slideUp with staggered delays (0.05s-0.1s increments).
- Live/active indicators use pulse animation.
- Transitions on interactive elements: transition all .2s or all .25s ease.
- Never use JavaScript for animations. CSS only.
- Keep animations subtle. Duration 0.3s-0.5s max. Never bouncy. Always ease or ease-out.

